{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"B\n    \n      Full Tool Visibility (Parallel Event Channel)\n      Add a WebSocket connection from Dragon to TinkerClaw's event system to get real tool names, args, and results. Then forward them to Tab5 as tool_call/tool_result messages (which voice.c already handles!).\n      \n        Dragon subscribes to TinkerClaw agent events via WebSocket (new connection alongside HTTP)\n        Receives: stream:\"tool\", phase:\"start\", name:\"web_search\", args:{query:\"...\"}\n        Forwards: {\"type\":\"tool_call\",\"tool\":\"web_search\",\"args\":{...}} to Tab5 (existing protocol!)\n        Tab5 already handles tool_call/tool_result in voice.c → shows \"Searching the web...\" in ui_voice.c\n        Plus everything from Option A (suggestions, model label, welcome card)\n      \n      \n        Changes: tinkerclaw_llm.py (WS event subscription, ~80 lines) + server.py (forward tool events) + ui_chat.c (cosmetic) + ui_voice.c (already handles tool_call!)\n        Objects: +5-6 | Risk: Medium — new WS dependency, but Tab5 side already done\n        Huge win: Tab5 voice.c already shows \"Searching...\", \"Calculating...\" for tool_call events","choice":"b","id":null,"timestamp":1776254579850}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"D\n    \n      Voice Orb Agent Cockpit\n      The voice overlay (ui_voice.c) transforms when in TinkerClaw mode. The orb becomes an agent status display. Tool activity shown as animated rings/text around the orb. Chat stays for text history.\n      \n        Orb color ring: Rose pulsing = thinking, amber flash = tool executing, green = speaking\n        Status label evolution: \"Listening...\" → \"Thinking...\" → \"Searching the web...\" → \"Found 3 results\" → \"Speaking...\"\n        Context ring: Thin ring around orb showing memory/tool activity count (like Apple Watch activity rings)\n        Tool name display: Below orb, shows current tool: \"web_search\" with animated dots\n        Requires tool visibility from Option B or C to show real tool names\n      \n      \n        Changes: ui_voice.c (orb state machine extensions, ~100 lines) + needs B or C for tool data\n        Objects: +4-6 (reuses existing orb objects) | Risk: Low — ui_voice.c already has the state machine\n        Voice-first: Most interactions are via orb, so this is where visibility matters most","choice":"d","id":null,"timestamp":1776254591731}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"E\n    \n      Combined: C + A + D (The Full Package)\n      The recommended approach. Three layers that build on each other:\n      \n        Layer 1 — SSE tool injection (C): Modify TinkerClaw's openai-http.ts to emit tool events in SSE. Dragon parses and forwards to Tab5. ~70 lines across 2 files.\n        Layer 2 — Smart Chat (A): Agent suggestions, model label fix, welcome card, tool activity bubbles inline. All in existing ui_chat.c.\n        Layer 3 — Voice Orb Cockpit (D): Orb shows tool names, animated status, rose theming. Uses tool events from Layer 1. All in existing ui_voice.c.\n      \n      \n        Changes: openai-http.ts + tinkerclaw_llm.py + server.py + ui_chat.c + ui_voice.c (all existing files)\n        Objects: +10-12 total | Risk: Medium — touches 3 repos but each change is small\n        Zero new files. Zero new screens. Zero new LVGL overlays.","choice":"e","id":null,"timestamp":1776254603627}
